<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="tune-n">tune <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tjuːn/    美 /tuːn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] 调子；曲调；旋律：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When I’m playing a sad tune, I am crying in my heart.
我演奏哀伤的乐曲时，自己内心也在哭泣。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2u">2.<strong>[U] 和谐</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-tune">in tune</h3>
<p>1.<strong>合调；协调：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sing in tune 
唱得合调</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>be in tune with the times 
跟上时代潮流</p></div>

<h3 id="out-of-tune">out of tune</h3>
<p>1.<strong>走调；不协调：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have no ear for music. My singing is out of tune.
我不懂音乐，唱歌总跑调。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>be out of tune with the times 
与时代格格不入</p></div></div>